# CI after push (blocking)

**A push is not done until CI is green** on that branch. Do not end the session, open a PR as ready, or mark work complete after `git push` without watching the run.

Workflow: `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — jobs **`python`** and **`frontend`** (both must succeed).

## After every push (required)

```bash
# From repo root; branch defaults to current
bash scripts/ci/watch_github_ci.sh [branch]
```

Or manually:

```bash
gh run list --branch <branch> --workflow ci.yml --limit 1
gh run watch <run-id> --exit-status
gh run view <run-id> --json conclusion,status,headSha,url
```

| Outcome | Action |
|---------|--------|
| **success** | Record run URL in PR / summary; proceed |
| **failure** | `gh run view <run-id> --log-failed` → fix → push again → re-watch |
| **User waives** | AskQuestion only; note waiver in PR/summary |

## Before the first push (local parity)

When changes touch Python, frontends, workflows, or secrets, run CI-equivalent checks locally:

```bash
uv sync --group dev
bash scripts/check_modal_no_database_url.sh
bash scripts/check_openapi_specs.sh
bash scripts/check_secrets.sh
bash scripts/check_no_operator_specs_tracked.sh
uv run ruff check apps packages tests
uv run ruff format --check apps packages tests
uv run basedpyright apps packages tests
uv run pytest tests/unit tests/integration tests/privacy tests/e2e tests/smoke tests/eval
cd apps/chat-rag-frontend && npm ci && npm run lint && npm test
cd apps/data-management-frontend && npm ci && npm run lint && npm test
```

## After merge to `main`

Watch CI on **`main`** for the merge commit (H0ci / 15-service-health). If `main` is red after your merge, fix in the same session before declaring deploy/health **PASS**.

## Do not

- Mark hotfix **resolved**, milestone **complete**, or PR **ready to merge** while CI is red on that branch.
- Ask the user to push without planning to watch CI afterward.

